# .docauthor

Hi, I'm Leo, a **Data Engineer** based in Italy. I build reliable data pipelines and cloud-based infrastructure, with a focus on automation, maintainability, and clean delivery workflows.

## Experience

I have a little over 3 years of experience as a Data Engineer. I'm currently based in northern Italy and work fully remotely at [Agile Lab](https://www.agilelab.it/) as a consultant for an international client in the vehicle manufacturing industry. Previously, I worked for [Kineton](http://www.kineton.it) as a consultant for an Italian client in the telecommunications sector.

Before that, I had the opportunity to take part in a research fellowship at the university where I studied, collaborating with the [Polis-Lombardia](https://www.polis.lombardia.it/wps/portal/site/polis) institute on a data science project focused on monitoring tweets for the analysis of events and diseases.

My academic background includes a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science and a Master's degree in Data Science.

For more: [Resume](/static/cv.pdf)


## Projects

I like working on side projects in my free time. Most of them never make it to the finish line, but these are the ones I'm proud of:

